<div id="post-2018" class="post-2018 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-boston tag-boston tag-mit tag-moving">
		<div class="date">
		<a href="http://www.pikachews.com/2014/09/a-number-of-things/" title="Permalink to A number of things" rel="bookmark">
							<p><span class="day">13</span>Sep / 2014</p>
					</a>
	</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<h1 class="entry-title">
							<a href="http://www.pikachews.com/2014/09/a-number-of-things/" title="Permalink to A number of things" rel="bookmark">A number of things</a>
					</h1>

		<div class="entry-content">
			<p>A number of things have occurred since <a href="http://www.pikachews.com/2014/05/salted-caramel-brownies/">we last spoke</a>.<br />
I’ve moved from the Greatest City in the World </p>
<p><a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/mpetitchou/15039484309" title="Untitled by mpetitchou, on Flickr"><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3916/15039484309_866d7cb908.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="Untitled"></a><br />
to one that’s not half bad.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/mpetitchou/15225939312" title="Untitled by mpetitchou, on Flickr"><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3879/15225939312_0bbf8901b0.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="Charles"></a><br />
I’m a <a href="http://blog.sophiechou.com/2014/racial-thinking-vs-racism/">student again</a>,<br />
and also a research assistant at a <a href="http://www.media.mit.edu/">pretty exciting place</a>.</p>
<p>Most notably, my new home comes with the dreamiest kitchen you’ve ever met:<br />
<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/mpetitchou/15039455948" title="Good morning from my new kitchen  #ibelieveinathingcalledlove by mpetitchou, on Flickr"><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3868/15039455948_40bddb3350.jpg" width="500" height="500" alt="Good morning from my new kitchen  #ibelieveinathingcalledlove"></a><br />
which means, I’ll be cooking a lot…<br />
especially since it’s my favorite way of dealing with stress.</p>
<p>Ciao!</p>
								</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	</div><!-- .content -->

